Output structure

All resumable functions store data under the working directory: BatchNews// BatchCases// BatchDockets//

Each folder contains: checkpoint.rds page_001.rds page_002.rds BatchCases_id_keyed.json

BatchNews Example

library(lexisbatch)
lexis_auth_env()

# Build query
q <- bn_new() |>
  bn_search("title(theranos OR elizabeth holmes)") |>
  bn_filter_date("2009-01-01", "2015-10-20") |>
  bn_expand(document = TRUE) |>
  bn_top(50)

# Debug final URL
bn_debug_url(q)
## [1] "https://services-api.lexisnexis.com/v1/BatchNews?%24search=title%28theranos%20OR%20elizabeth%20holmes%29&%24select=ResultId%2CTitle%2CDate&%24filter=Date%20ge%202009-01-01%20and%20Date%20le%202015-10-20&%24expand=Document&%24top=50&%24count=true"
# Fetch automatically with checkpointing
news <- bn_fetch_resumable_auto(q)
## Resuming with 331 seen ids.
##   | Page 1 (raw 50, new 0) | cum new=331/331
##   | Page 2 (raw 50, new 0) | cum new=331/331
##   | Page 3 (raw 50, new 0) | cum new=331/331
##   | Page 4 (raw 50, new 0) | cum new=331/331
##   | Page 5 (raw 50, new 0) | cum new=331/331
##   | Page 6 (raw 50, new 0) | cum new=331/331
##   | Page 7 (raw 31, new 0) | cum new=331/331
# Output stored in:
# BatchNews/title_theranos_OR_elizabeth_holmes/

If the process stops or fails mid-run, just re-run:

# news <- bn_fetch_resumable_auto(q)

It will resume from the last saved page automatically.

BatchCases Example

library(lexisbatch)
lexis_auth_env()

q <- bc_new() |>
  bc_search("roe vs wade") |>
  bc_filter_date("1965-01-01","1980-12-31") |>
  bc_expand(document = TRUE) |>
  bc_top(50)

bc_run_resumable_auto(q)
## Resuming BatchCases with 11 seen ids.
##   | Page 1 (raw 11, new 0) | seen=11/11
## == Using inline XML from column: Document.Content

BatchDockets Example

library(lexisbatch)
lexis_auth_env()

qd <- bd_new() |>
  bd_search("1:22cv859") |>
  bd_filter_date("2022-01-01","2022-12-31") |>
  bd_top(50)


dck <- bd_run_full_resumable(qd)
## Resuming dockets with 21 seen IDs.
## [DEBUG URL] https://services-api.lexisnexis.com/v1/BatchDockets?%24search=1%3A22cv859&%24select=ResultId&%24filter=Date%20ge%202022-01-01T00%3A00%3A00Z%20and%20Date%20le%202022-12-31T23%3A59%3A59Z&%24top=50&%24count=true
##   | IDs page 1 | raw=21, new=0, seen now=21/21
## No new IDs  no new XML to fetch.
## == Parsing XML  JSON for all saved dockets ...

Common Parameters Argument Description page_sleep Pause between API pages to respect rate limits retry, retry_wait Retry on HTTP 429/500/503 fetch_xml Whether to download XML documents parse_xml Whether to parse XML into JSON parallel_xml Fetch XML concurrently using furrr workers Number of parallel workers base_dir Custom output folder write_json File path to save parsed JSON

Reading saved data

You can reload data at any time:

rows <- readRDS("BatchNews/title_theranos_OR_elizabeth_holmes_/page_001.rds")
json <- jsonlite::read_json("BatchCases/roe_vs_wade/roe_vs_wade_id_keyed.json")
